message:
@jimhull, Regarding your latest article on the ridiculous practice of stating the goal out loud, I wanted to share with you a short passage from "Save the Cat", probably the most popular screenwriting book of late. This is from page 146:

"Is what your hero wants obvious to you and to the audience? If not, or if you don't know what your hero's goal is, figure it out. And make sure the goal is spoken aloud and restated in action and words throughout the story."

Sigh.
